The article discusses President Trump's stance on free trade and his actions to address what he believes are unfair trade practices. It highlights the impact of trade agreements such as NAFTA and China's admission to the World Trade Organization on American manufacturing jobs. The article argues that previous politicians have not been honest about the consequences of these agreements and praises Trump for questioning the "gospel of free trade." It also mentions the concerns of Wall Street investors and the push by some auto workers for American-made products. Overall, the article suggests that Trump has a mandate from his supporters to act on trade issues.